                        flask, and also how to measure the pH of the solution
                        using a pH meter or pH paper. <br><br>

                        Materials required: <br>
                        • Acid or base (for example, hydrochloric acid, sulfuric
                        acid, sodium hydroxide, or potassium hydroxide)<br>
                        • Distilled water <br>
                        • Volumetric flask<br>
                        • pH meter or pH paper<br>
                        • Stirring rod<br> <br>
                        Procedure:<br>
                        1. Rinse the volumetric flask with distilled water to
                        remove any impurities.<br>
                        2. Measure the desired volume of acid or base using a
                        graduated cylinder and pour it into the volumetric
                        flask.<br>
                        3. Add distilled water to the volumetric flask until it
                        reaches the marked level on the flask.<br>
                        4. Mix the contents of the flask using a stirring rod.<br>
                        5. Measure the pH of the solution using a pH meter or pH
                        paper.<br><br>
                        Observations:<br>
                        • The acid or base dissolves in water to form a clear
                        solution.<br>
                        • The pH of the solution can be measured using a pH
                        meter or pH paper.<br><br>
